parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the check engine light to illuminate, leading to potential engine damage, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions. In some cases, it may also cause a burning smell or visible smoke.

The refusal of dealerships to honor the recall can lead to owners being left with the financial burden of repairing or replacing the faulty camshaft position sensor, potentially causing financial hardship and decreased trust in the manufacturer.
symptoms: Dealership refuses to perform recall repair
citing reasons such as incorrect part number or lot number
or lack of availability of parts.
